Description: mod loader / plugin framework for the Proxmox VE web UI
 pve-modkit is a mod loader (plugin framework) for the Proxmox VE web
 interface, not a single theme. It injects a small loader script into the PVE
 UI and serves author-provided "mods" -- self-contained folders of JavaScript
 and assets -- from /usr/share/pve-modkit/mods/ via a dedicated /modkit/ static
 route registered in pveproxy. Many mods (themes, badges, tweaks, userscripts)
 can be installed side by side; dropping a mod folder in makes it load
 automatically on the next page load.
 .
 The web-UI patches (index.html.tpl and pveproxy.pm) are applied idempotently,
 validated by the real Template Toolkit and Perl parsers, backed up
 byte-for-byte, re-applied on upgrade via dpkg triggers, and cleanly reverted
 on removal -- so you never hand-hack stock pve-manager files. Ships one subtle
 default mod (a "modkit: active" badge beside the version header) to confirm
 the loader is live; fuller demo mods live in the source tree and are not
 installed.
